I want to talk about hormonal acne, but first we need to talk about THE PILL. 

I had been on and off the pill (mostly on) from the age of 16 and after doing a lot of research, I finally made the decision to get off the pill a few months ago. I had been wanting to get off of it for a while, but the main thing holding me back was the fear of getting hormonal acne again (I had it during one of the times I got off the pill previously). I had a solid skincare routine and my skin was healthy and almost entirely acne-free, so I thought I’d be safe from getting any pimples. Well, a few months in I broke out pretty much overnight with painful cystic hormonal acne around my chin area. My first reaction was panic. My skin had been so clear for YEARS and I remembered how much I hated having acne and how insecure it made me. 

But you know what else happened after I got off the pill? My personality came back. All the sudden I had so much more energy! My mood swings lessened! I felt overall more happy, more energetic and most of all, more myself. I realized that acne will go away eventually, and I’ve been researching holistic ways to heal my hormones internally which I plan to document. Having my personality back, feeling normal again, not constantly feeling like I’m on a rollercoaster of massive ups and huge lows is worth a few pimples. Getting off the pill was the best decision I’ve made for myself. It’s also a huge personal decision and this was my own experience, everybody is different so please seek professional advice before making any decisions, but I wanted to share my own story! 

#hormonalacne #birthcontrolproblems #birthcontrol #cysticacne

so many new friends here recently so thought I’d reintroduce myself! 

I was born and raised in San Diego but have been traveling on and off for the last 6 months with my boyfriend James. We just recently got a van so lookout for van life content coming soon 👀 

I love all things health and wellness but I’m a huge advocate for living a balanced life. I love going to the gym but I also equally love going to festivals or grabbing dinner and drinks with friends. I am the wellness girl that is going to say yes to the tequila shot. 

I’ve struggled with social anxiety my whole life but over the years I’ve handled it much better! I do still have days where it comes back with a vengeance though. 

I finally started a podcast this year - something I’d wanted to do forever! @onawhim.podcast is all about navigating life as a 20-something year old. 

I love being outside and in nature. The ocean is where I feel most myself, and I am a beach/summer/tropical island girl through and through. 

I have a flemish giant rabbit named Reggie but he also goes by Wiggy, Squilliam, Reg, and Squigward. 

I share pretty much everything on here. Workouts, outfits, recipes, what I’m reading, what I’m thinking, etc etc, nothing is off limits here so welcome and I hope you stay awhile 🤍

According to a study, it takes an average of 66 days for a habit to become automatic. 

Operation 66 is not just another health challenge; it is designed to help you build life-long healthy habits so that you can become the best version of yourself. 

There are just 6 simple habits to follow each day for 66 days (just a little over 2 months!):

- drink 16oz of water first thing in the morning
- 45 minutes of movement + 10 minutes of stretching 
- journal and/or meditate 
- follow a 90/10 diet
- limit social media to one hour 
- spend a minimum of one hour on a personal goal or hobby 

I have never been so productive and felt so good before! I can’t wait to see where I’m at by the end of this challenge.
